GEN_description: Pirgopolinice, the miles gloriosus which gives the title to the comedy of the same name, is just the most famous of the boastful soldiers who populate Plautus' opera. He's in love with the beautiful Philocomasio and opposes her love for Pleusicle, but after deceptions and plot twists that involve the servants of the two contenders, his ego will be beaten, soundly and literally.With Caterina Mordeglia, Lecturer of History of Latin Theatre at the University of Trento

GEN_description: This masterpiece of the baroque theatre was written in 1635. With the burlesque character of Matamore, who hinders the love between Clindor and Isabelle, Corneille offers us a variation on the theme of the swaggering and vainglorious captain of classical descent.Curated by Paolo Tamassia, Lecturer in French Literature at the University of Trento
